name: Run tests after non-trivial changes
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Making changes without running tests afterward
then: Run tests immediately after any non-trivial change, especially to domain methods or API endpoints
why: Frequent testing catches regressions early and ensures code quality.
globs: ["src/**/*.py", "tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Save test_main.py output with descriptive names
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Running test_main.py without saving output to tests/output/
then: Save output to tests/output/test_main_output_new.txt and compare with baseline
why: Enables regression testing and identifies unexpected changes in system behavior.
globs: ["tests/test_main.py"]

---
name: Compare test outputs with baseline
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Not comparing new test output with test_main_output1.txt baseline
then: Compare new output with baseline and report any differences immediately
why: Output differences likely indicate a problem that needs investigation.
globs: ["tests/test_main.py"]

---
name: Test domain methods with session management
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Testing domain methods without proper session setup/teardown
then: Include session management in tests to match production usage patterns
why: Tests must accurately reflect how code runs in production.
globs: ["tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Test both success and error scenarios
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Only testing happy path scenarios
then: Test error conditions, edge cases, and invalid inputs
why: Comprehensive testing ensures robust error handling and edge case coverage.
globs: ["tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Test API endpoints with proper HTTP status codes
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: API tests without checking HTTP status codes
then: Verify correct status codes (200, 201, 400, 404, 500) in API tests
why: Proper HTTP status codes are critical for frontend integration.
globs: ["tests/test_api_endpoints.py"]

---
name: Test calculated field computations
scope: python
language: python
severity: warning
if: Not testing calculated fields like equity balances, totals, or tax amounts
then: Add specific tests for calculated field accuracy
why: Calculated fields are critical for financial accuracy and user trust.
globs: ["tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Use descriptive test names
scope: python
language: python
severity: info
if: Test function names that don't describe what they test
then: Use descriptive names like test_add_capital_call_updates_equity_balance
why: Clear test names make debugging easier and serve as documentation.
globs: ["tests/**/*.py"]

---
name: Test component rendering and interactions
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: React components without tests
then: Write tests using React Testing Library for component rendering and user interactions
why: Component tests ensure UI behavior matches requirements and catches regressions.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.spec.tsx"]

---
name: Mock external dependencies in tests
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Tests that make real API calls or use real dependencies
then: Mock fetch API, React Router hooks, and other external dependencies
why: Isolated tests are faster, more reliable, and don't depend on external services.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.spec.tsx"]

---
name: Test loading states and error handling
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without tests for loading and error states
then: Test loading indicators, error messages, and error recovery
why: Loading and error states are critical for user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.spec.tsx"]

---
name: Commit only after tests pass
scope: python
language: python
severity: error
if: Attempting to commit changes without running tests
then: Run all relevant tests and ensure they pass before committing
why: Prevents broken code from being committed and maintains code quality.
globs: ["**/*"]
